### **DIRECTOR'S ASSESSMENT**

This quarter's cycle has successfully identified the two critical components 
requiring immediate sourcing action (controller_board_v3 and 
harness_assembly_a). The **Helix award for controller_board_v3** is commercially
sound, operationally safe, and ready for human approval—it restores inventory 
buffer before the 3-week production risk window closes.

The **Meridian exclusive proposal** presents an interesting cost-saving 
opportunity (22% reduction) but carries material strategic risk (single-source 
lock-in, $2M sunk capital, no quality gates) that hinges on supplier financial 
stability and annual volume forecasts I do not possess. I have escalated this 
appropriately to strategic governance (CFO/VP Supply Chain) with a clear 
negotiator assessment recommending modified terms (phased commitment, shorter 
exclusivity, performance gates, escrow) if the company wishes to pursue it. 
**Helix can proceed in parallel while Meridian deliberation continues.**

The **harness_assembly_a sourcing** is well-positioned with Arc Wirecraft 
(proven, capacity-constrained supplier) but requires urgent qualification of a 
secondary source to eliminate the single-source capacity risk that market 
intelligence flagged.

**Next steps**: (1) Human approval of Helix $398k award; (2) CFO strategic 
review of Meridian proposal; (3) Procurement identification and evaluation of 
secondary source for harness_assembly_a; (4) Finalize contracts once approvals 
resolve.
